#: ../../game_variants.rst:5
msgid "Game Variants"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:7
msgid ""
"Sometimes new game variants are proposed on the internet or in fat pack's "
"booklet. This document gathers all that information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:10
msgid "Wizard's Tower"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:12
msgid ""
"**A Magic Variant for 2-5 Players.** (Appeared in Theros fat pack booklet.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:14
msgid ""
"Wizard's Tower is a fun way for you and your friends to explore the set - "
"and everything you need to play is in this fat pack! In this casual format, "
"all players share a single library, also known as the \"Tower,\" and they "
"draft a card in addition to their normal draw for the turn."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:17
msgid "**Starting the game:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:19
msgid ""
"Open the nine booster packs and the land pack in this fat pack. (Try not to "
"look at the cards in the boosters yet, though. It's more fun to discover "
"them during the game.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:21
msgid "Shuffle all the cards together into a huge deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:22
msgid "Determine randomly who will go first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:23
msgid "Deal three cards to each player."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:24
msgid ""
"Starting with the first player, each player may discard any number of cards "
"and redraw that many. Once all players have done this, shuffle the discarded "
"cards and put them on the bottom of the deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:26
msgid ""
"Put the top seven cards of the deck face up in the middle of the table. The "
"deck becomes a library that's shared by all players."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:29
msgid "**Playing the game:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:31
msgid ""
"When playing Wizard's Tower, your draw step gets a bit more interesting:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:33
msgid ""
"First, choose one of the face-up cards and add it to your hand. If there "
"aren't any, put the top seven cards of the tower face up in the middle of "
"the table, and then choose one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:36
msgid "Draw the top card of the tower."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:37
msgid ""
"All players share the same library and the same graveyard. If you cast a "
"spell that targets a card in an opponent's graveyard or manipulates the top "
"card of your library, those cards affect the shared library or graveyard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:40
msgid "The face-up cards aren't considered to be in any game zone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:42
msgid ""
"Other than that, the game is played as a Free-for-All **Magic** game. The "
"last player left standing wins!"
msgstr ""
